					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 17th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper.</support>
								<extent>289 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>152</height>
										<width>102</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>120</height>
										<width>80</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>289 folios (+ 2 paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 6 leaves each.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Folios missing after folio 1, 3, 5, 6, 104, 272.</p>
									<p>Slightly stained.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="17" writtenLines="17">
									<p>Uniform layout. Visible ruling with a mastara.</p>
									<p>Initial words of each section written in larger characters, preceded with a title page (see e.g. folio 1r, 6r, etc).</p>
									<p>Catchwords on every verso.</p>
									<p>The biblical verses are given with punctuation.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Square and semi-cursive Oriental script of the 17th century. <name type="person" role="scribe">Avraham ben Mordekhai ha-Kohen</name>: inscribed in volume 2, folio 220v, and volume 3, folio 126v. Avraham ha-Kohen wrote the present manuscript for his son, Yosef. The name of the latter is inscribed under the title of each Muḳadimah.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">[...] ben Yeshu῾ah Firūz</name>: inscribed, folio 2r of volume 1. </p>
